    <ThingDef ParentName="MechResourceBase">
    <defName>TW_DoxaTacticalCore</defName>
    <label>Fire Suppression Tactical Core</label>
    <useHitPoints>false</useHitPoints>
    <description>"Strategic Core: Fire Suppression Warfare" - residual processor from Doxa-0. Contains neural architectures for fire control computation, target prioritization, and battlefield suppression algorithms. Features exceptional data throughput, parallel processing, and full compilation support for mechanoid structures/implants.

Enables construction of mechanoid units, deployment structures, and specialized equipment. Functions as advanced implant control hub for "tactical self-evolution" - essential for mastering mechanoid battlefield tempo in Total War systems.</description>
    <graphicData>
      <texPath>Things/DoxaTacticalCore</texPath>
      <graphicClass>Graphic_Single</graphicClass>
    </graphicData>
    <statBases>
      <Flammability>0</Flammability>
      <DeteriorationRate>0</DeteriorationRate>
    </statBases>
    <comps>
      <li Class="CompProperties_CompAnalyzableUnlockResearch">
        <analysisID>996</analysisID>
        <requiresMechanitor>true</requiresMechanitor>

        

        <analysisDurationHours>0.5</analysisDurationHours>
        <destroyedOnAnalyzed>false</destroyedOnAnalyzed>
        <completedLetterLabel>Doxa Tactical Core studied: {RESEARCH} unlocked</completedLetterLabel>
        <completedLetter>通过研究压制火控战略核心，{PAWN_labelShort}获得了{RESEARCH}研究项目所需的深层认知与技术洞见。

您的科研团队现在可以使用研究台开始探索如何实际应用这项技术。</completedLetter>
        <completedLetterDef>PositiveEvent</completedLetterDef>

        

        <activateTexPath>UI/Icons/Study</activateTexPath>
        <activateLabelString>Analyze...</activateLabelString>
        <activateDescString>Analyze the Tactical Core.</activateDescString>
        <jobString>Analyze Doxa Tactical Core</jobString>
        <guiLabelString>Choose who should analyze this</guiLabelString>
        <inspectString>Can be analyzed by a colonist.</inspectString>

        <targetingParameters>
          <canTargetBuildings>false</canTargetBuildings>
          <canTargetAnimals>false</canTargetAnimals>
          <canTargetMechs>false</canTargetMechs>
          <onlyTargetControlledPawns>true</onlyTargetControlledPawns>
        </targetingParameters>
      </li>
    </comps>
  </ThingDef>
  
  <ThingDef ParentName="MechResourceBase">
    <defName>TW_ArmorBlitzWarfare</defName>
    <label>Armor Blitz Strategic Core</label>
    <useHitPoints>false</useHitPoints>
    <description>"Strategic Core: Armor Blitz Warfare" - legacy tactical engine from the Shell Fortconstruct. Contains all mechanoid ground assault and fire advancement algorithms. Records include vehicle path optimization, target suppression protocols, area prioritization, and multi-layer defense coordination - embodying the "frontal suppression, heavy penetration" doctrine.

Recovery and analysis unlocks heavy-assault mechanoid units/structures and enables development of high-strength composite armor with active feedback systems. Also functions as implant control module to enhance mechanized lifeform survivability and assault capabilities - key to achieving "firepower breakthrough" in Total War systems.</description>
